# Generation 8: identity & self-reflection — answered from the self-model
# the agent wrote into its own KB at birth (derived from real state).
> who are you?
< I am parrot0.
> what are you?
< I am parrot0.
> do you exist?
< Yes, I am parrot0.
# Capabilities are reported from the ACTUAL registry, reified as facts.
> what can you do?
< My modules are: memory, self, knowledge, greet, farewell.
# The reflexive payoff: the self-model is queried by the SAME logic engine as
# world knowledge — "who is a module?" resolves over module(X).
> who is a module?
< memory, self, knowledge, greet, farewell.
# Ordinary world knowledge still works alongside the self-model.
> socrates is a man
< Learned: man(socrates).
> who is a man?
< socrates.
